race.comment: Tricky affair over the 3000m. EAGLE ANGEL (1) has mixed his form of late, awful two back at Flemington when surely too bad to be true, better last time at this track over 2400m and giving every indication he'd handle the extra 600m. He's lightly raced on a quick backup which can see him elevate again. HANAFUBUKI (3) is a frustrating conveyance who is struggling to win, stuck on the 2 from 19. She often leaves herself with too much to do but should stay the trip well and prove hard to hold out again. HIGHLAND GLORY (8) is another with a poor winning record but she's going okay and is another that looks like she'll stay strongly. URBAN OUTLOOK (4) was well backed at Geelong when finding a slowly run affair. He was going well prior and can improve.
